Date: 0/0/1935
Source: Slang Today
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 287
Edition:
Quote:  I'll admit I was stiff when I lost that fifty francs, but my cobber produced another ten; and when the ring-keeper said `Up and do 'em', I collected 200 francs. ...How did yo get down here, Joe? Joe. Well, I was so stiff I nearly turkeyed off from the line, but I decided to wait. <i>Ibid.</i> 288  ... it's time we all took a tumble to ourselves and discussed something pleasant, say a little party. A. I'm stiff. C. How are you holding, D? D. All right.
Notes: 1935 A.E. Strong WW1 scene in Partridge Slang Today 287

