Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 107
Edition:
Quote: <i>stiff</i> unlucky, often expressed sarcastically in such phrases as <i>stiff luck, stiff cheese, stiff cheddar</i>; eg `I've just eaten the last sausage roll. Stiff cheese, old boy. Teach you to be late.' NZA.
